Nakuru Town West MP Samuel Arama will be charged with abuse office and land-related corruption matters, DPP Noordin Haji has said. Arama spent the night in custody after he was arrested on Friday night by Ethics and Anti-graft agency officers. In a statement on Saturday, Haji noted that Arama will be charged on Monday with conspiracy to defraud, making a document without authority. Others are; Uttering a document with intent to deceive, obtaining registration of land by false pretences and knowingly misleading an investigator. According to Haji, there was a complaint from a member of the public in relation to the manner in which Arama acquired a plot in Nakuru municipality. "The outcome of investigations revealed that Arama in collusion with officers in the Nakuru lands registry unlawfully and deceitfully caused illegal registration and issuance of a certificate of lease," he said, Arama is being held at Nakuru Railways Police Station. His brother Charles Arama said the MP was arrested at b.30pm alongside his lawyer. Read:Â MP Samuel Arama arrested over land fraud